1. Kada *dolazila* sam u grad, uvek sam se sastajala sa prijateljima. (When I used to come to the city, I always met up with friends.)
2. Ona je *dolazila* kasno na posao, pa su je kolege upozoravale. (She used to arrive late to work, so her colleagues would warn her.)
3. Da li si primetio da je stalno *dolazila* na isto mesto u parku? (Did you notice that she always came to the same spot in the park?)
4. Kada bih *dolazila* kući sa fakulteta, mama bi me čekala sa toplom večerom. (When I would come home from college, my mom would wait for me with a warm dinner.)
5. U toku dana, *dolazila* su mi razna pitanja od kolega. (Throughout the day, different questions would come to me from my colleagues.)
6. Šta si mislio kad si rekao da je ona *dolazila* svakog dana u školu? (What did you mean when you said she used to come to school every day?)
7. Kad sam *dolazila* do prodavnice, setila sam se da sam zaboravila novčanik. (When I got to the store, I remembered that I forgot my wallet.)
8. Oduvek mi se sviđao taj kafić jer su uvek *dolazile* zanimljive osobe. (I always liked that café because interesting people would always come.)
9. Bila sam jako umorna kada sam *dolazila* kući, pa sam odmah otišla da se odmorim. (I was very tired when I came home, so I went straight to rest.)
10. Ne znam koliko dugo sam *dolazila* do tog mesta dok se nisam jednom izgubila. (I don't know how long I used to come to that place until I got lost once.)